==English==
===Etymology===
Old French [[martel]] (modern [[marteau]]), from mediæval Latin [[martellus]], from Latin [[martulus]], a varient of [[marculus]] ‘small hammer’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mɑ:təl/

===Noun===
'''martel'''
# a [[hammer]], especially a [[warhammer]]

